13:00.451 --> 13:04.562
Ladies and gentlemen,
this is not a case about a cop.

13:04.587 --> 13:05.995
This is a case

13:06.020 --> 13:09.840
about a civilian that
just wanted to protect us.

13:09.936 --> 13:12.258
Guys, put yourself in
Danny's shoes, okay?

13:12.283 --> 13:15.647
You're alone. It's nighttime.
You're in the jungle.

13:15.673 --> 13:18.414
Something jumps out at you.
It's gonna get you!

13:18.438 --> 13:20.308
It's gonna kill you! You're dead!

13:20.537 --> 13:24.229
Afraid, right?

13:24.364 --> 13:27.370
Wouldn't you defend yourself?

13:27.395 --> 13:29.353
Wouldn't we all?

13:29.774 --> 13:31.099
Hell, yeah, we would!

13:31.124 --> 13:32.995
Hell, yeah, we would!

13:33.202 --> 13:35.702
So, let's do the right thing now,

13:35.848 --> 13:37.870
and let's let this man go free.

13:37.896 --> 13:39.864
That's a great speech.

13:39.889 --> 13:41.924
[Applause]

13:42.505 --> 13:45.695
Okay, let me get this straight.

13:46.560 --> 13:49.929
You're not a police officer?

13:49.954 --> 13:52.452
No, Karen, I am not.

13:52.509 --> 13:54.072
No, you're worse.

13:54.097 --> 13:56.845
You're a liar with a gun!

13:56.870 --> 13:59.204
He lied to us.

13:59.229 --> 14:01.570
Liar with a gun. LWG.

14:01.595 --> 14:04.033
- Objection.
- Karen: We trusted him with our gun!

14:04.058 --> 14:05.585
He could have shot any of us!

14:05.610 --> 14:08.469
I say we banish him!

14:08.494 --> 14:10.311
[Indistinct shouting]

14:10.336 --> 14:12.193
Is this part of your plan?

14:12.218 --> 14:14.227
Nope.

14:17.725 --> 14:21.090
Bruce: We're just going over the
same material over and over again.

14:21.115 --> 14:22.314
You guys!

14:22.339 --> 14:24.139
We've been at this for hours, okay?

14:24.164 --> 14:26.226
It's Danny. It was an accident.

14:26.251 --> 14:28.010
Roger: Unless it wasn't.

14:28.035 --> 14:31.283
I think we should do an eye for an eye,
bullet for bullet.

14:31.308 --> 14:32.825
Holy shit, Roger.

14:32.850 --> 14:34.850
Look, I just plain don't trust Pack.

14:34.875 --> 14:36.473
I'm not saying he's a terrorist,

14:36.498 --> 14:39.287
but what was he doing on our plane?
He might be a terrorist.

14:39.312 --> 14:41.133
No, hey! Man, Pack's my buddy,

14:41.158 --> 14:43.661
and the... the real
terrorist is the gun...

14:43.686 --> 14:45.354
- Okay.
- So why don't we banish the gun?

14:45.379 --> 14:48.199
Look, you're ruining this island,
Cat Stevens! That's what you have here!

14:48.224 --> 14:49.778
- [Indistinct shouting]
- Hey, look!

14:49.819 --> 14:52.889
We're clearly not gonna come
to any conclusions tonight,

14:52.914 --> 14:56.424
so why don't we just get some shut-eye,
and we'll start first thing in the morning.

14:56.449 --> 14:59.070
- We're...  We're sleeping here?
- Yeah, Missy. We're sequestering.

14:59.102 --> 15:02.253
Florence: <i>Number two...
Never, ever, ever, ever</i>

15:02.278 --> 15:03.640
<i>be alone with Chet after dark.</i>

15:03.664 --> 15:06.070
I hope you guys like it Au naturel

15:06.095 --> 15:07.519
'cause I sleep in the buff.

15:07.544 --> 15:12.237
[REO Speedwagon's
"Keep On Loving You" plays]

15:12.262 --> 15:14.544
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

15:14.569 --> 15:16.189
What if there was another way?

15:16.213 --> 15:18.163
A way that ends this now?

15:18.189 --> 15:21.057
♪

15:21.480 --> 15:23.772
Well, has the jury reached a verdict?

15:23.797 --> 15:25.638
We have.

15:26.124 --> 15:29.272
We, the jury,
have decided that Danny's fate...

15:29.823 --> 15:32.025
♪

15:32.611 --> 15:34.860
Shall be decided by Steve.

15:35.138 --> 15:37.104
Are you [bleep] kidding me right now?

15:37.129 --> 15:39.836
It was the only unanimous
decision we could come to.

15:39.861 --> 15:42.611
I mean, always be sequestering,
like, day and night,

15:42.636 --> 15:44.234
and sleeping together and stuff.

15:44.259 --> 15:45.503
We all trust Steve.

15:45.528 --> 15:47.214
He will do what's best for the island.

15:47.239 --> 15:48.996
You are making him a dictator.

15:49.021 --> 15:50.745
Come on, Owen. It's just Steve.

15:50.771 --> 15:52.242
Yeah, and I'm sure in Germany,

15:52.267 --> 15:54.248
they were like, "Come
on. It's just Adolf!"

15:54.272 --> 15:55.841
Oh. Oh. Oh. Oh.

15:55.867 --> 15:59.060
It's the mustache, isn't it?
That's where the comparison ends.

15:59.085 --> 16:02.347
Maybe that and my love of fine art.

16:02.372 --> 16:05.508
Well, if that's what the,
uh, island has decided,

16:05.533 --> 16:07.162
then so be it.

16:07.187 --> 16:08.590
I'm gonna make a decision.

16:08.615 --> 16:10.892
I'll be back in an hour.

16:10.917 --> 16:12.417
[Indistinct talking]

16:12.442 --> 16:14.476
[Insects chirping]

16:14.977 --> 16:17.976
♪

16:18.437 --> 16:20.886
[Sighs]

16:21.208 --> 16:22.509
Jessaroni!

16:22.534 --> 16:24.084
- Oh! God. Shit.
- Sorry.

16:24.109 --> 16:26.043
I didn't mean to spook you. I'm sorry.

16:26.067 --> 16:28.034
Chet, we cannot keep doing this, okay?

16:28.059 --> 16:29.642
We-We've got to stop.

16:30.477 --> 16:33.916
Oh, you're developing feelings for me.

16:33.941 --> 16:35.431
What? No.

16:35.456 --> 16:37.003
- No?
- No.

16:37.028 --> 16:38.036
Oh.

16:38.062 --> 16:40.910
Y-You're interested, though,
like, you kind of want to...

16:40.935 --> 16:42.935
- Not really.
- Not really?

16:42.960 --> 16:43.940
No.

16:43.965 --> 16:47.567
Okay, do you...
Do you like me at all, or...

16:48.253 --> 16:51.206
No. no!

16:51.231 --> 16:54.080
I don't like you at all, Chet!

16:54.106 --> 16:55.372
Oh, my God!

16:55.396 --> 16:56.745
You're the worst.

16:56.769 --> 16:58.976
You're not funny. You're not smart.

16:59.002 --> 17:00.938
You're kind of sweaty all the time,

17:00.963 --> 17:02.291
and honestly, I don't understand

17:02.316 --> 17:03.848
most of the weird things that you say,

17:03.872 --> 17:05.728
because...
I-It's not because I don't get it.

17:05.753 --> 17:07.278
It's because it's literally gibberish.

17:07.303 --> 17:08.940
It just...  It doesn't make sense, Chet!

17:08.964 --> 17:11.300
- Mm.
- Huh.

17:11.334 --> 17:13.901
So if I don't have feelings for you,

17:13.925 --> 17:16.501
where does that leave us?

17:17.665 --> 17:23.011
- ♪ Keep on loving you ♪
- [Both moaning, shouting]

17:24.101 --> 17:25.800
This isn't right, Steve.

17:25.825 --> 17:26.904
[Sighs]

17:26.929 --> 17:29.490
You just can't stand the idea
of me being in charge, can you?

17:29.515 --> 17:30.635
In charge of what?

17:30.660 --> 17:32.121
You're playing make-believe here.

17:32.146 --> 17:33.844
This is not a real society.

17:33.869 --> 17:35.928
This is just some rock
that we're stuck on

17:35.953 --> 17:37.747
until we can get home.

17:38.376 --> 17:42.431
Owen, this is our reality,
and I'm the leader here.

17:42.456 --> 17:45.689
Well, then, do the
right thing for Danny.

17:45.714 --> 17:49.178
I promise you, I will.

17:53.327 --> 17:54.582
Yolonzo?

17:54.607 --> 17:56.542
Yolonzo!

17:56.567 --> 17:58.181
Yolonzo?

18:02.525 --> 18:05.181
I knew it was Mengshu! Yes!

18:05.206 --> 18:09.609
I am so sorry, Yolonzo, but I knew it.

18:09.634 --> 18:11.548
[Laughs]

18:11.573 --> 18:13.464
[Coughing]

18:21.515 --> 18:23.181
[Steve sighs]

18:23.216 --> 18:25.291
This was not an easy decision.

18:25.316 --> 18:27.339
It was an honest one.

18:27.417 --> 18:30.018
What we're trying to do here
on this island is difficult.

18:30.230 --> 18:33.265
We're laying the foundation
for a real society

18:33.290 --> 18:36.024
because this is not some
rock we're living on.

18:36.060 --> 18:37.359
This is home.

18:38.421 --> 18:40.820
And when you're at home,
you want to feel safe.

18:40.845 --> 18:43.179
Now, do I think that Danny is dangerous?

18:43.204 --> 18:44.403
No.

18:44.428 --> 18:46.325
Therefore, he will not be banished.

18:46.349 --> 18:48.597
- [Sighs]
- [Crowd murmuring]

18:48.622 --> 18:51.924
But the fact does remain
that he did lie to us,

18:52.237 --> 18:55.805
and his lie resulted in
a severe injury to Pack.

18:55.913 --> 18:59.578
So therefore, Danny,
I give you three weeks in the pit.

18:59.603 --> 19:01.973
Wow. Great job.

19:01.998 --> 19:05.376
- And, Owen, you'll be joining him.
- What?!

19:05.401 --> 19:08.203
You were complicit in his
lies since the very beginning.

19:08.228 --> 19:10.428
- Makes you an accomplice.
- This is insane.

19:10.453 --> 19:12.767
Just serve the time, Owen.

19:12.792 --> 19:15.427
Do the right thing.

19:16.069 --> 19:19.937
Okay, Steve, how about you
take a big shit into your hands

19:19.962 --> 19:21.853
and then eat it with your own face?

19:21.878 --> 19:23.654
'Cause we're not gonna go in your pit.

19:23.680 --> 19:25.113
- [All gasping]
- A bit foul.

19:25.968 --> 19:27.935
But don't make me think of banishment

19:27.961 --> 19:29.580
because I'm...  I'm gonna consider it.

19:29.605 --> 19:31.612
Owen, please,
if we're both in the pit together...

19:31.637 --> 19:32.329
It's okay.

19:32.354 --> 19:34.540
Yeah, you don't have
to consider it, okay?

19:34.565 --> 19:37.865
Because right now,
I'm banishing myself and Danny

19:37.890 --> 19:40.845
because we would rather go live
on the other side of this island

19:40.871 --> 19:43.705
and focus on what's important,
which is getting home.

19:43.730 --> 19:46.179
Once you leave, you can never return.

19:46.204 --> 19:47.595
No, I understand what banishment is

19:47.620 --> 19:49.023
'cause I just banished myself.

19:49.048 --> 19:51.432
- Right.
- Danny, you ready to go?

19:53.020 --> 19:55.610
Daniel, you don't have
to listen to this.

19:55.635 --> 19:57.350
He's... He's confused, I think.

19:57.375 --> 19:58.681
If I was you, I'd stay.

19:58.706 --> 20:02.154
We've got a nice, warm pit here for you.

20:03.216 --> 20:05.291
Okay, let's go.

20:05.316 --> 20:07.923
[Dramatic music plays]

